pack-track
Homonym Number:
Word Class:noun
Sense Number: 1
Definition:a narrow track cut through bush or rock wide enough only to accommodate a pack-horse or pack-bullock.
Origin:[none]
Register:
Register 2:
Flag: Farm Words
Domain:Rural
Region:[none]
